The men were part of a gang that apparently tried to hold up a cellphone shop on Wednesday afternoon. CAPE TOWN Police have confirmed four people have been arrested after an attempted robbery Riverside Mall in Rondebosch. The men were part of a gang that apparently tried to hold up a cellphone shop on Wednesday afternoon. Two gunmen are on the run. Officers from the Rondebosch police station a few metres from the shopping centre responded to an alarm activated during the attempted heist. The police's Andre Traut said: This afternoon the swift response of the Rondebosch police station resulted in the arrest of four suspects. The police responded to a report of a robbery in progress at a cellphone shop at the Riverside Mall. The four suspects were arrested after they fired shots at the police. 